main event: Multiple bright lights of various colors were observed in the sky over Hankins, New York on November 3, 1966.
interesting points: The objects had blinking and pulsating lights, but did not exhibit any erratic maneuvers.
The objects would disappear and reappear several times during the observation.
The observer, a hotel owner, felt the lights were likely glidden UFOs.
No physical evidence or photographs were obtained.
The weather conditions at the time were clear with good visibility.
sighted object: Bright red, green, orange, and white lights in the sky
